  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0dad\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0da0\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dad\u0dc0\u0dba \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0dcf \u0daf\u0d9a\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The American ambassador condemns the violence",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "US Ambassador to Sri Lanka Ms. Julie Chang has stated in a statement that she condemns all forms of violence against peaceful protesters and journalists.",
        "In her statement, the American Ambassador has also requested a full investigation into the violent incidents and property damage related to the protests and to enforce the law against all those involved in them.",
        "Stating that she is closely monitoring the current political situation in Sri Lanka, the American ambassador also says that thousands of people from all walks of life have come to the streets for accountability, transparency and a better future for all Sri Lankans.",
        "Stating that this is a dangerous, threatening and important moment in the history of Sri Lanka, she urges the parliament to allow the parliament to work for the good of the whole nation for the good of one political party and for that, all parties should act with restraint and respect."
      ],
